data.text: Vinyl LP pressing. Many of the tracks on Songs in the Dark were sung to the pair at bedtime when they were children, ergo the inclusion of several lullabies. In addition to their own musical family tree, the folk-flecked album also includes the Wainwright Sisters' "dark, mysterious, and beautiful" take on number made famous by Woody Guthrie and Jimmie Rogers.
